      "writtenOn": "2019-08-20T20:47:46Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Oh, I see what you’re doing with ZLIB_CONST. Don’t do this. Hopefully these snippets from \u003czconf.h\u003e and \u003czlib.h\u003e will show you how ZLIB_CONST and const in zlib are intended to work.\n\n\u003czconf.h\u003e:\n\n#if defined(ZLIB_CONST) \u0026\u0026 !defined(z_const)\n#  define z_const const\n#else\n#  define z_const\n#endif\n\n// …\n\n#  define FAR\ntypedef unsigned char  Byte;  /* 8 bits */\n   typedef Byte  FAR Bytef;\n\nSo:\n - z_const is #defined as “const”\n - Bytef is a type alias for unsigned char\n\n\u003czlib.h\u003e:\n\ntypedef struct z_stream_s {\n    z_const Bytef *next_in;     /* next input byte */\n    // …\n\nSo:\n - decltype(z_stream_s::next_in) is const unsigned char*",
      "revId": "63b48be5011d66d7869b002877a353d6f8a471ae",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
